In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients; mix well. Shape into four patties. In a large greased skillet over medium heat, brown patties on both sides; drain. Add pineapple and juice, green pepper and onions; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes. In a small bowl, combine vinegar, water, brown sugar and cornstarch; mix well. Add to pineapple mixture. Bring to a boil; boil and stir for 2 minutes. Serve over rice.